cs.NA, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SC, cs.MS 

This paper deals with numerical analysis of a specific algorithm for solving large scale linear systems, which is a topic in numerical analysis (cs.NA). The algorithm is designed to hide communication latency on massively parallel hardware, which is a topic in distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the effect of local rounding errors on convergence, which is a topic in numerical analysis and scientific computing (cs.SC). The use of recurrence relations is a topic in discrete mathematics and combinatorics (cs.DS). Finally, the numerical experiments conducted in the paper involve testing the algorithm on different problem sizes and hardware configurations, which is a topic in modeling and simulation (cs.MS).
